Just a heads up that the files in aries contain \r\n flags for new lines. Windows doesn't recognize the \r character but it can be removed easily from all files using ```
 find . -mindepth 1 -type f -exec sed -i 's/\r//g' {} \;
``` from a bash command line (in my case git bash)

