the ZKPs that are supported in the protocol are basically that you can require that a certain attribute has an integer value >= a given value.. so anything you want to check if someone is 18 and you have the DOB the credential would need to use e.g. epoch date.. so you cannot use a string notation for the date if you want to use ZKPs. 

/// predicate_info: Describes requested attribute predicate
///     {
///         "name": attribute name, (case insensitive and ignore spaces)
///         "p_type": predicate type (Currently >= only)
///         "p_value": predicate value
///         "restrictions": Optional<wql query>,
///         "non_revoked": Optional<<non_revoc_interval>>, // see below,
///                        // If specified prover must proof non-revocation
///                        // for date in this interval this attribute
///                        // (overrides proof level interval)
///     }

