Follow up to the discussion today. The "extra" fields in the did:key DIDDoc are NOT in the JSON-LD context.  Using the URL that was referenced (https://w3id.org/did/v1) resolves to this - https://w3c-ccg.github.io/did-spec/contexts/did-v1.jsonld  and none of those fields (`assertionMethod`, `capabilityDelegation`, `capabilityInvocation` and `keyAgreement`) are in that context document.

So - @drummondreed no need to panic about the context - the list looks reasonable. 

